text: William Dumas (born 23 January 1942 in Nîmes) was a member of the National Assembly of France from 2004 to 2017. He represented the 5th constituency of the Gard department, and is a member of the Socialiste, radical, citoyen et divers gauche. ==References== Category:1942 births Category:Living people Category:People from Nîmes Category:Socialist Party (France) politicians Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
title: William Dumas
